SIMPLE: passing
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Passing
<hw>Pass"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of one who,
or that which, passes; the act of going by or away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Passing bell</b></col>, <cd>a tolling of a bell to
announce that a soul is passing, or has passed, from its body (formerly
done to invoke prayers for the dying); also, a tolling during the
passing of a funeral procession to the grave, or during funeral
ceremonies.</cd> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au>
<au>Longfellow.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Passing
<hw>Pass"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to the act of
passing or going; going by, beyond, through, or away;
departing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exceeding; surpassing, eminent.</def>
<au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Her <xex>passing</xex> deformity.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Passing note</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a character
including a passing tone.</cd> -- <col><b>Passing tone</b></col>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a tone introduced between two other tones, on an
unaccented portion of a measure, for the sake of smoother melody, but
forming no essential part of the harmony.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Passing
<hw>Pass"ing</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Exceedingly; excessively;
surpassingly; <as>as, <ex>passing</ex> fair; <ex>passing</ex>
strange.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧You apprehend <xex>passing</xex>
shrewdly.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passingly</ent>⟦br⟧
